=== RAW MODEL ANSWER ===
Answer: Step 1: Convert 2-amino-5-(methoxycarbonyl)benzoic acid (or its acid chloride) to 2-amino-5-(methoxycarbonyl)benzamide. | Step 2: Cyclocondense this anthranilamide with a one-carbon formyl source (e.g. formamide or HC(OEt)3/NH3) to give 7-methoxycarbonylquinazolin-4(3H)-one. | Step 3: Chlorodehydrate the 4-oxo heterocycle with POCl3 to form 4-chloro-7-methoxycarbonylquinazoline. | Step 4: Perform SNAr with 3,4,5-trimethoxyaniline to obtain 4-(3,4,5-trimethoxyphenyl)amino-7-methoxycarbonylquinazoline. | Step 5: N-alkylate the quinazoline ring nitrogen with tert-butyl (3-bromopropyl)carbamate (or the corresponding tosylate) under basic conditions to give the N-(3-Boc-aminopropyl) methyl ester intermediate. | Step 6: Hydrolyze the methyl ester (LiOH/NaOH/KOH, aq. THF/MeOH) while retaining Boc to furnish the target COc1cc(Nc2nc3ccc(C(=O)O)cc3n2CCCNC(=O)OC(C)(C)C)cc(OC)c1OC.

